OL,6,FAccording to Smokefree Action, in the
OL,7,Fyear following the introduction of
OL,8,Fsmoke-free laws there was a 2.4%
OL,9,Freduction in hospital admissions for
OL,10,Fheart attacks in England, which saved
OL,11,Fthe NHS #8.4 million in the first year
OL,12,Falone.
OL,14,FThe first year after the introduction
OL,15,Fof the indoor smoking ban, also saw a
OL,16,F12.3% reduction in hospital admissions
OL,17,Ffor childhood asthma.
